==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nocturn
<hw>Noc"turn</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>nocturne</ets>, fr. L. <ets>nocturnus</ets>. See
<er>Nocturnal</er>, and cf. <er>Nocturne</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>An office of devotion, or act of religious service, by
night.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One of the portions into which the Psalter was
divided, each consisting of nine psalms, designed to be used at a night
service.</def> <rj><au>Hook.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nocturnal</ent>⟦br⟧
